🔷 Common System Design Patterns (Industry Use) ?
1️⃣ Layered Architecture Pattern (Basic) : Application ko layers me divide karna. Architecture:

Controller Layer
   |
Service Layer
   |
Repository / DAO Layer
   |
Database

2️⃣ Microservices Architecture Pattern ⭐ (Most Important) :
Application ko small independent services me tod dena.Full Architecture:

Client
  |
  v
Load Balancer
  |
  v
API Gateway
  |
  +-------------------+
  |                   |
User Service     Order Service     Payment Service
  |                   |                   |
 User DB           Order DB           Payment DB




1. vertical scalling ?
vertical scalling me aap apne physical server/ computer ke resources ko increase krte ho.
it has one problem that is down time:- chlti machine ke resources ko increase/add nhi kr skte.
solution: doing horizental scalling.

2. horizental scalling :- isme aap same server ke replica ko add krte ho, but dns always has fixed ip to even replica krne ke bad v client ka request dns ko hee jayega isliye ek or server
   add krte hai jo loadbalancer (jo ki design pattern hota h) hota h, jo decide krta hai kon se replica ko request jayega.
 DNS (Domain Name System):-Human-readable name → Machine-readable IP address eg- www.paytm.com  →  34.120.45.67 :- Hum website ka naam yaad rakhte hain,computer/server ko IP address chahiye.
                           DNS ke pass us domain ka ip map hota hai.


